<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,324,1454,1480]" box="[189,324,1454,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1454,1480]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1454,1480]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Comments</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1400,1501,1707]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">
This is a small genus with seven named species that are restricted to the Eastern Mediterranean from 
<collectingCountry box="[190,275,1537,1563]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Greece</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[315,422,1537,1563]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
. The new species collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[794,842,1538,1564]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Iran</collectingCountry>
represent the southeasternmost records of the genus. Compared to other gnaphosids, homology of the male palpal structures in this genus is unclear, as it is questionable whether the sclerotized hook-like structure (“posterior hook” sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Panayiotou E. &amp; Kaltsas D. &amp; Seyyar O. &amp; Chatzaki M." pageId="2" pageNumber="70" pagination="44 - 54" refId="ref18061" refString="Panayiotou E., Kaltsas D., Seyyar O. &amp; Chatzaki M. 2010. Revision of the genus Berinda (Araneae, Gnaphosidae) in the east Mediterranean with the description of two new species. Zootaxa 2362: 44 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2362.1.2" type="journal article" year="2010">
Panayiotou 
<emphasis box="[1340,1397,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
) that guides the tip of the embolus is a greatly modified median apophysis or not. Here, we treat the hook-like structure as a median apophysis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[188,1400,1747,2025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">
While comparing our specimens to the species reported from Europe, we realized that 
<taxonomicName authority="Lissner, 2016" authorityName="Lissner" authorityYear="2016" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berinda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="idae">
<emphasis box="[1244,1400,1747,1773]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Berinda idae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lissner J. &amp; Chatzaki M." box="[191,349,1783,1809]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" pagination="9 - 11" refId="ref17628" refString="Lissner J. &amp; Chatzaki M. 2016. A new species of Berinda (Araneae, Gnaphosidae) from the eastern Aegean Islands, Greece. Arachnologische Mitteilungen 51: 9 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.5431 / aramit 5102" type="journal article" year="2016">Lissner, 2016</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(described from 
<collectingCountry box="[548,631,1783,1809]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Greece</collectingCountry>
and later reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[915,1002,1783,1809]" name="Cyprus" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Cyprus</collectingCountry>
) is undoubtedly a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872)" baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[220,773,1819,1845]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Heser" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infumatus">
<emphasis box="[220,412,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Heser infumatus</emphasis>
(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872)
</taxonomicName>
(from 
<collectingCountry box="[852,938,1819,1845]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[948,1057,1819,1845]" name="Tanzania" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1067,1137,1819,1845]" name="Egypt" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Egypt</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1192,1261,1819,1845]" name="Israel" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Israel</collectingCountry>
; introduced to 
<collectingCountry box="[221,293,1855,1881]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Japan</collectingCountry>
). The copulatory organs are identical (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lissner J. &amp; Chatzaki M." box="[791,1094,1855,1881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" pagination="9 - 11" refId="ref17628" refString="Lissner J. &amp; Chatzaki M. 2016. A new species of Berinda (Araneae, Gnaphosidae) from the eastern Aegean Islands, Greece. Arachnologische Mitteilungen 51: 9 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.5431 / aramit 5102" type="journal article" year="2016">Lissner &amp; Chatzaki 2016</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2–3 and 
<bibRefCitation author="Levy G." box="[1262,1395,1855,1881]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" pagination="93 - 158" refId="ref17565" refString="Levy G. 1998. The ground-spider genera Setaphis, Trachyzelotes, Zelotes, and Drassyllus (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) in Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology 44: 93 - 158." type="journal article" year="1998">Levy 1998</bibRefCitation>
: figs 112–115) and both have been recorded from Greek islands. The long filiform embolus, robust conductor and distinctive tibial apophysis conform to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Roewer" authorityYear="1928" box="[851,947,1926,1952]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berinda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[851,947,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Berinda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName authority="Tuneva, 2004" authorityName="Tuneva" authorityYear="2004" box="[1097,1341,1927,1953]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Heser" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1097,1168,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Heser</emphasis>
Tuneva, 2004
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Panayiotou E. &amp; Kaltsas D. &amp; Seyyar O. &amp; Chatzaki M." box="[191,458,1962,1989]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" pagination="44 - 54" refId="ref18061" refString="Panayiotou E., Kaltsas D., Seyyar O. &amp; Chatzaki M. 2010. Revision of the genus Berinda (Araneae, Gnaphosidae) in the east Mediterranean with the description of two new species. Zootaxa 2362: 44 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2362.1.2" type="journal article" year="2010">
Panayiotou 
<emphasis box="[328,387,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Thus, a generic transfer is proposed, resulting in the new combination 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zamani &amp; Chatzaki &amp; Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1872" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berinda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="infumatus" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="70">Berinda infumatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[312,442,1998,2025]" pageId="2" pageNumber="70" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1872).
</paragraph>
